description:
People queue up for a ride at an amusement park, and VIP pass holders can skip the line.

Implement a priority queue to manage the ride queue with VIP priority.

Example
Input: 4 People: [P1, VIP1, P2, VIP2]

Output: Queue: [VIP1, VIP2, P1, P2]

Explanation:
VIP pass holders are given priority in the queue.

Edge Case
Input: 2 People: [P1, P2]

Output: Queue: [P1, P2]

Input Format:

The first line contains an integer n — the number of people in the queue.

The next n lines contain the names of the people, where VIP pass holders have the prefix "VIP".

Output Format:

Print the names of the people in the final queue, with VIPs at the front.

Constraints:

1 ≤ n ≤ 10^5

The names of the people will only contain alphanumeric characters and have a maximum length of 10 characters.
title: Amusement Park Ride Management
